    box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  }</style><div class="jump-button-container" style="display: none;">
<button id="jump-to-recipe-btn">Jump to Recipe ↓</button></div> <script src="data:text/javascript;base64," defer type="pmdelayedscript" data-cfasync="false" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1" data-no-minify="1"></script> </div><div class="gb-element-0c3895e4"><div class="dynamic-entry-content"><div class='hb-ad-inpage'><div class='hb-ad-inner'><div class='hbagency_cls hbagency_space_237303' id='hbagency_space_237303_0'></div></div></div><p>Let&#8217;s talk about mornings. Sometimes they feel like a race against the clock, right? You want something tasty, something that feels like a treat, but you also need it to be good for you and not take forever to make. If that sounds like you, then you&#8217;re in the right place. We&#8217;re diving into some fantastic <strong>breakfast ideas</strong> that are seriously going to make your mornings brighter.</p><p>Specifically, we&#8217;re whipping up a High <a href="https://nutritionsource.hsph.harvard.edu/what-should-you-eat/protein/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Protein</a> Cottage Cheese Cinnamon Roll Bread. Think of your favorite cinnamon rolls, but in a soft, moist loaf form, loaded with protein, and super simple to put together. No fancy stuff needed, just good ingredients for a great start.</p><div class='hb-ad-inpage'><div class='hb-ad-inner'><div class='hbagency_cls hbagency_space_237303' id='hbagency_space_237303_1'></div></div></div><div class="gb-element-5c204a46"><div class="wp-block-rank-math-toc-block" id="rank-math-toc"><p> Jump To:</p><nav><ul><li class=""><a href="#the-easiest-ninja-creami-sorbet-recipes-youll-make-all-summer">The Easiest Ninja Creami Sorbet Recipes You&#8217;ll Make All Summer</a></li><li class=""><a href="#essential-ingredients-for-ninja-creami-sorbets">Essential Ingredients for Ninja Creami Sorbets</a></li><li class=""><a href="#how-to-make-any-fruit-sorbet-in-the-ninja-creami-step-by-step">How to Make Any Fruit Sorbet in the Ninja Creami (Step-by-Step)</a></li><li class=""><a href="#our-top-5-ninja-creami-sorbet-recipes">Our Top 5 Ninja Creami Sorbet Recipes</a></li><li class=""><a href="#pro-tips-for-the-best-sorbet-every-time">Pro Tips for the Best Sorbet Every Time</a></li><li class=""><a href="#troubleshooting-common-sorbet-issues">Troubleshooting Common Sorbet Issues</a></li><li class=""><a href="#your-sorbet-adventure-awaits">Your Sorbet Adventure Awaits</a></li></ul></nav></div></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Why You&#8217;ll Love This Recipe</h2><p>This recipe is a true winner for so many reasons. It&#8217;s incredibly moist and has that comforting cinnamon swirl we all adore. Plus, it packs over 20 grams of protein per slice, which is amazing for keeping you full and energized.</p><div class='hb-ad-inpage'><div class='hb-ad-inner'><div class='hbagency_cls hbagency_space_237303' id='hbagency_space_237303_2'></div></div></div><p>It’s a fantastic way to use cottage cheese in a new and exciting way. Forget bland breakfasts; this is a protein sweet breakfast that tastes like dessert but is perfect for kickstarting your day.</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Ingredients</h2><h3 class="wp-block-heading">For the Bread</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>1¼ cups cottage cheese (blended until smooth)</li><li>1 large egg</li><li>2 tbsp maple syrup or honey</li><li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li><li>2 cups oat flour (or almond flour for <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/nutrition-and-healthy-eating/in-depth/gluten-free-diet/art-20048530" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">gluten-free</a>)</li><li>1 tsp baking powder</li><li>¼ tsp baking soda</li><li>Pinch of salt</li></ul><h3 class="wp-block-heading">For the Cinnamon Swirl</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>⅓ cup coconut sugar or brown sugar</li><li>2 tbsp melted butter or coconut oil</li><li>1½ tsp cinnamon</li></ul><h3 class="wp-block-heading">For Optional Glaze</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>½ cup powdered sugar</li><li>1–2 tbsp blended cottage cheese or Greek yogurt</li><li>Splash of vanilla or milk to thin</li></ul><h2 class="wp-block-heading">Step-By-Step Instructions</h2><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Prep Your Oven and Pan</h3><p>First things first, let&#8217;s get that oven preheating to 350°F. Grab your loaf pan and give it a good greasing. For extra easy removal, line it with parchment paper. Trust me, this little step saves you a headache later.</p><div class='hb-ad-inpage'><div class='hb-ad-inner'><div class='hbagency_cls hbagency_space_237303' id='hbagency_space_237303_3'></div></div></div><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Smooth Out the Cottage Cheese</h3><p>Now, take your cottage cheese and pop it into a blender or food processor. You want it super smooth. No lumps allowed! This is key to getting that lovely, soft texture in our <strong>protein breads</strong>.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Combine Wet Ingredients</h3><p>In a big bowl, whisk together that smooth cottage cheese, your egg, maple syrup (or honey, if you prefer), and vanilla extract. Give it a good mix until everything is well combined.</p><div class='hb-ad-inpage'><div class='hb-ad-inner'><div class='hbagency_cls hbagency_space_237303' id='hbagency_space_237303_4'></div></div></div><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Mix Dry Ingredients</h3><p>In a separate bowl, combine your oat flour, baking powder, baking soda, and a pinch of salt. Whisk them together so everything is evenly distributed.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Form the Batter</h3><p>Time to bring it all together. Stir your dry ingredients into the wet mixture. It&#8217;ll form a pretty thick batter. Don&#8217;t worry, that&#8217;s exactly what we want for this kind of loaf.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Make the Cinnamon Swirl</h3><p>In a small bowl, mix up your cinnamon swirl ingredients: coconut sugar (or brown sugar), melted butter (or coconut oil), and cinnamon. Stir until it&#8217;s a nice, spreadable paste.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Layer the Batter and Swirl</h3><p>Pour about half of your batter into the prepared loaf pan. Then, spoon half of the cinnamon mixture over the top. Give it a gentle swirl with a knife or spoon.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 8: Repeat and Swirl Again</h3><p>Now, add the rest of the batter, followed by the remaining cinnamon mixture. You can swirl this layer a bit more, creating those beautiful marble patterns. Just be gentle so you don&#8217;t overmix.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 9: Bake the Loaf</h3><p>Pop that loaf pan into your preheated oven. Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes. You&#8217;ll know it&#8217;s done when a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Let it cool in the pan for a bit before you try to remove it.</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Step 10: Glaze It Up (Optional)</h3><p>If you&#8217;re feeling fancy, whip up the optional glaze. Just mix the powdered sugar, a couple tablespoons of blended cottage cheese or Greek yogurt, and a splash of vanilla or milk until it&#8217;s smooth. Drizzle it over your cooled bread. It adds a lovely touch!</p><div class="gb-element-1b1baf03"><div class="gb-element-69e0d888"><h3 class="gb-text gb-text-751fcd90"><strong><a href="https://www.cookfastrecipes.com/pastries/" data-type="category" data-id="1">More Pastries</a></strong></h3></div><div class="gb-element-a6a1e935"><div><div class="gb-looper-1938e437"><div class="gb-loop-item gb-loop-item-b81e556d post-10276 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-pastries no-featured-image-padding">
